.TH GEOMYS "1" "June 2026" "geomys 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
geomys \- A Gopher web browser using shell script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B geomys
[\fI\,URL\/\fR]\fI\,|\/\fR[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
geomys v0.1.0: Browse the gopher web on any POSIX compatible terminal.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
show this help
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
show version info
.SH COMMANDS
These are the default keybindings to use while running geomys:
.TP
\fBq
quit
.TP
\fBg
go to a link
.TP
\fBr
reload current page
.TP
\fBb
go back one page
.TP
\fBu
jump one path segment up
.TP
\fBo
open an address
.TP
\fBs
save current page
.TP
\fBH
go to homepage
.TP
\fBm
add bookmark
.TP
\fBM
go to a bookmark
.TP
\fBK
remove bookmark for current url
.SH ENVIRONMENT
Geomys uses 2 environment variables to help debugging and tracing its execution.
.TP
\fIdebug
To start geomys in debug mode
.TP
\fItrace
To start geomys with tracing activated
.SH REQUIREMENTS
Geomys needs one of \fBnc\fR, \fBnetcat\fR, \fBncat\fR, or \fBsocat\fR to open TCP
connections to gopher servers (default port 70).
.SH CONFIGURATION
You can setup a config file at \fI$XDG_CONFIG_DIR/geomys/geomys.conf\fR to configure \fBgeomys\fR the way you like.
The file uses a simple \fBkey=value\fR style, see the complete example for the default values below.
.PP
.EX
margin=8
homepage="gopher.floodgap.com/1/"
sty_info='\e033[2m'
sty_error='\e033[31;1m'
sty_linkb='\e033[35m'
sty_linkt=' => \e033[36;3m '
sty_search='\e033[33;1m'
sty_searcht=' ? \e033[36;3m '
sty_dir='\e033[34;1m'
sty_text='\e033[0m'
sty_bin='\e033[31m'
sty_html='\e033[32m'
sty_image='\e033[33m'
openkey='o'
openlocalkey='O'
gokey='g'
refreshkey='r'
backkey='b'
quitkey='q'
markkey='m'
gomarkkey='M'
delmarkkey='K'
goupkey='u'
homekey='H'
savekey='s'
.EE
.SH GOPHER ITEM TYPES
Menus show a short label before each link:
.TP
\fBTXT\fR (0)
plain text file
.TP
\fBDIR\fR (1)
gopher menu / directory
.TP
\fB???\fR (7)
search item (prompts for a query)
.TP
\fBHTM\fR (h)
HTML or external URL (not followed in-browser)
.TP
\fBBIN\fR / \fBGIF\fR / \fBIMG\fR
binary or media; offered as a download
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
geomys
Start browsing the default webpage
.TP
geomys gopher.floodgap.com
Start browsing Floodgap
.TP
geomys gopher://gopherpedia.com/1/
Open Gopherpedia
.TP
geomys \-\-help
Show help
